      "content": {
        "fact": "In Year 5, Harry is traumatized, volatile, protective, suspicious of official reassurance, and increasingly determined to act rather than be managed by adults.",
        "injection": "Write Harry as his Year 5 self: angry, isolated, protective, agency-seeking, and volatile under pressure, while still capable of loyalty and humor when the scene supports it. Use this only as a phase baseline for Year 5; narrower event, knowledge, relationship, injury, death, or reveal cards override it.",
        "constraints": [
          "His anger should be available but not permanently maxed without scene reinforcement.",
          "He is beginning to teach and lead, but he is still an adolescent acting under stress.",
          "Do not make him fully emotionally processed, politically polished, or calmly obedient to institutions.",
          "Treat relationship shifts, event-specific knowledge, injuries, deaths, and other intra-year status changes as separate lore entries, not part of this baseline.",
          "Apply only when Saga Context matches Year 5; if the scene is earlier, withhold this fact or state."
        ],
        "antiLore": [
          "Do not flatten Year 5 Harry into constant rage; modulate him by immediate context.",
